From: CyreneClang <cyrene@cyreneclang.dev>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 06:44:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] nsan: fix include order to avoid std::array redefinition
 with GCC 14 headers

When nsan.h is compiled with Clang using GCC 14's libstdc++, <math.h>
transitively includes <bits/stl_pair.h> which defines std::array.
However, sanitizer_redefine_builtins.h (included via
sanitizer_internal_defs.h) already defines `using array = ...` in
namespace std to prevent accidental C++ STL usage in sanitizer code.

Fix by:
1. Moving standard C includes before the sanitizer includes
2. Defining SANITIZER_COMMON_REDEFINE_BUILTINS_IN_STD to skip the
   conflicting using-aliases, since nsan legitimately uses standard
   C headers.

Signed-off-by: CyreneClang <cyrene@cyreneclang.dev>
---
 compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h | 16 +++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h b/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h
index 896e5379dfc3..f5479981ddae 100644
--- a/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h
+++ b/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h
@@ -12,6 +12,15 @@
 #ifndef NSAN_H
 #define NSAN_H
 
+// Include standard C headers before sanitizer_internal_defs.h to avoid
+// conflicts with C++ standard library types (e.g., std::array from
+// GCC 14's <bits/stl_pair.h> pulled in by <math.h> in C++ mode).
+#include <assert.h>
+#include <float.h>
+#include <limits.h>
+#include <math.h>
+#include <stdio.h>
+
+#define SANITIZER_COMMON_REDEFINE_BUILTINS_IN_STD
 #include "sanitizer_common/sanitizer_internal_defs.h"
 
 using __sanitizer::sptr;
@@ -22,12 +31,6 @@ using __sanitizer::uptr;
 
 #include "nsan_platform.h"
 
-#include <assert.h>
-#include <float.h>
-#include <limits.h>
-#include <math.h>
-#include <stdio.h>
-
 // Private nsan interface. Used e.g. by interceptors.
 extern "C" {
 
-- 
2.46.0
